value.title: Trump's voter-fraud remarks draw criticism from some Republicans
value.excerpt: President Trump faced some pushback from his own party Thursday after warning about illegal voting and an attempt to "steal" the presidential election.

value.title: Graham announces $500G donation to Trump campaign legal efforts, calls Philly elections 'crooked as a snake'
value.excerpt: Senate Judiciary Committee Chairman Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., told "Hannity" Thursday he will donate $500,000 to the Trump campaign's legal efforts to challenge election procedures in multiple states, including Pennsylvania, Michigan and Nevada.

value.title: Trump touts gains with minorities and women: 'We're the party of inclusion'
value.excerpt: President Trump touting his party’s gains with women and minorities, declared the Republican Party the “party of inclusion” in a news conference Thursday.

value.title: Trump campaign ballot counting lawsuits: What to know
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign has filed multiple lawsuits in Pennsylvania, Michigan, Georgia and Nevada as the race remains increasingly tight -- seemingly in favor of a Democratic candidate Joe Biden win.

value.title: Trump vows to challenge Biden wins in swing states: 'We will win'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Thursday swore that his campaign would continue to file legal challenges in states where Democratic nominee Joe Biden is projected to win, as the path for Trump to reach 270 electoral votes, the number necessary to win the presidency, continues to narrow.

value.title: 'Trump agenda won up and down the ballot' as pundits and polls missed the mark again: Kellyanne Conway
value.excerpt: The pollsters and pundits got the 2020 presidential race wrong yet again, Kellyanne Conway, former Trump 2016 campaign manager, told "Fox & Friends."

value.title: Biden's 1 electoral vote from Nebraska district could prove pivotal to his White House bid
value.excerpt: Omaha, Neb., became “Jomaha” as Democratic nominee Joe Biden won a single electoral vote from the state’s 2nd Congressional District.

value.title: 'Squad' member Ilhan Omar rejects Trump's Pennsylvania victory claim: 'Sit down'
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., on Wednesday criticized Eric Trump for claiming victory in Pennsylvania.

value.title: Trump was 'correct' that election would be 'much closer' than most thought: Frank Luntz
value.excerpt: President Trump and his pollsters were “correct” in saying that the 2020 presidential election would be "much closer" than anybody expected, veteran Republican pollster Frank Luntz said Wednesday.

value.title: McCarthy expects four more years for Trump after 'a very strong' election night
value.excerpt: House Minority Leader Rep. Kevin McCarthy, R-Calif., praised the work President Trump has done for the country and the Republican party, and predicted that after the final vote counts are complete the president will be reelected.

value.title: AOC says Trump’s claims of victory are 'illegitimate, dangerous'
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y., slammed President Trump after he declared victory in Tuesday's election despite millions of votes still being counted in key battleground states as of Wednesday morning.

value.title: Media and polls 'hyper-judgmental' of Trump supporters: Candace Owens
value.excerpt: Conservative activist Candace Owens slammed the media and pollsters for once again failing to accurately predict the presidential election.

value.title: AOC sounds alarm over Latino turnout for Biden
value.excerpt: Democratic U.S. Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez vented her frustrations over lackluster Democratic turnout among Latinos Tuesday evening.

value.title: Trump narrows gap in heavily Latino Texas county that Clinton won by 79%
value.excerpt: President Trump has made up a lot of ground in Starr County, Texas, since 2016 in what once a Democratic stronghold, according to results from the Texas Secretary of State's Office.

value.title: Twitter flags Trump tweet warning Democrats 'trying to steal' the election as 'misleading'
value.excerpt: President Trump tweeted that Democrats are “trying to STEAL the Election,” while claiming a “big win”—a post that Twitter flagged as “misleading” content.

value.title: Ex-ESPN host Jemele Hill says 'it's on White people' if Trump wins reelection: 'No one else'
value.excerpt: ESPN host Jemele Hill declared Tuesday that only White people are to blame if President Trump defeats Democratic nominee Joe Biden.

value.title: Biden surrogate Coons says campaign is 'cautiously optimistic' about election results
value.excerpt: The Biden campaign is "cautiously optimistic" heading into election night and believes it will ultimately come out ahead in the key battleground of Pennsylvania, one of its surrogates told Fox News.

value.title: Ex-Gov. and Ex-Inmate Rod Blagojevich Votes, Trump Having Commuted Sentence
value.excerpt: Former Illinois Gov. Rod Blagojevich cast his first ballot Tuesday since President Trump [earlier this year]( commuted his 14-year sentence for multiple corruption crimes. He voted a split ticket. “It

value.title: Colorado Sen. Michael Bennet not interested in being Biden's education secretary
value.excerpt: Colorado’s senior Democratic senator has said he would not be interested in serving as education secretary under a prospective Joe Biden’s administration, despite his background in public education.

value.title: CNN's Don Lemon hits network for airing Trump's 'propaganda' visit to RNC office
value.excerpt: CNN anchor Don Lemon questioned the judgment of his own network Tuesday after it broadcast remarks President Trump made during his visit to a Republican National Committee office.

value.title: In St. Petersburg, Fla., Trump's Character Is in Focus
value.excerpt: With millions of Floridians having already voted, the Election Day line quickly diminished outside the largest polling location in St. Petersburg, Fla. The city resides in Pinellas County, one of the bellwether counties in the country's largest battleground state.

value.title: Trump May Try to Fire Wray, but FBI Director Has GOP Support on Capitol Hill
value.excerpt: President Trump has frequently and openly speculated about firing FBI Director Christopher Wray after the election, but Mr. Wray continues to enjoy support from some GOP senators..

value.title: Trump thanks campaign staffers, predicts 'incredible night': 'Tremendous group of people'
value.excerpt: The president spoke for a time to campaign staff and answered questions from the media before hitting the road again.

value.title: Ex-Trump loyalist Michael Cohen hints former boss won't like his ballot choice
value.excerpt: President Trump's former attorney trolled the White House with a Twitter hint that he voted for Democrat Joe Biden.

value.title: Trump says US is 'most difficult country to deal with,' reflecting on battles with Pelosi, Schiff
value.excerpt: President Trump on Tuesday said the United States is the "most difficult country to deal with" as he reflected on his time as president during an Election Day interview on "Fox & Friends."

value.title: John Legend appears to jab at Trump fans Ice Cube, Lil Wayne during rally for Kamala Harris
value.excerpt: John Legend appears to be shading a few colleagues in the music industry.  During a final rally for Democratic vice presidential nominee Sen. Kamala Harris in Philadelphia, Legend took the stage to perform with fellow artist Common,

value.title: Trump says Supreme Court decision on Pennsylvania ballots is 'dangerous,' 'will 'induce violence'
value.excerpt: President Trump Monday called a Supreme Court decision that said Pennsylvania could allow mail ballots through Friday “dangerous,” adding it would lead to “violence.”

value.title: Sen. Kennedy calls Trump 'an insult to the political elite' who never 'talks down' to the working class
value.excerpt: The devotion of Donald Trump voters to their candidate stems from two factors, Sen. John Kennedy, R-La., told "Tucker Carlson Tonight" Monday.

value.title: Biden to campaign in Pennsylvania, Harris to Michigan on Election Day
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden will travel to Pennsylvania Tuesday while his running mate Sen. Kamala Harris will campaign in Michigan, in their final push to get out the vote on Election Day.

value.title: President Trump installs commission to promote 'patriotic education,' counter 'radical' views of US history
value.excerpt: President Trump signed an executive order Monday designed to promote what he called "patriotic education" and to push back on the idea that the country is "irredeemably and systemically racist."
